div.p:
The whole civilized world has as much interest in the monographiae
A. de Candolle & C. de Candolle (1878-96). as in the "prodromus";
A. P. de Candolle (1823-73). and if you sent to each Government a Circular , asking for a subsidy by subscribing for a number of copies, you would have more fund at command, the monographiae could proceed with more celerity , as the printer could add specially for the purpose to his establishment. It is much to be regretted, that such grand, cosmopolitan publication did hitherto not get the status of an international one, to which each Government should give a proportionate extra - support . As the present arrangements are, it must take half a century , to finish the monographiae.
